[2] Cholera - Angola (Luanda)
Date: Thu, 23 Mar 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Angola Press [edited]
<http://www.angolapress-angop.ao/noticia-e.asp?ID=427208>

1 person died out of 65 new cases of cholera registered in the last 24
hours, as the epidemic outbreak worsens in the Angolan capital, Luanda.
The Health Provincial Director, Vita Vemba, said that 43 cases had been
notified at Sambizanga, 20 at Boavista and 2 at Cazenga, totalling 18
deaths in 551 cases since the epidemic started in 13 Feb 2006.
Sambizanga municipality alone has registered 280 cases, surpassing
Ingombotas, the municipality where the outbreak started.
Vita Vemba has expressed concern over the occurrence of cases at Cazenga
for being the most populous municipality with around 1 million inhabitants
and presenting major basic sanitation problems.
--
