[5] Cholera - Uganda (Arua)
Date: Tue, 21 Mar 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: AllAfrica.com and The Monitor (Kampala) [edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/200603201104.html>

After a 1-week lull, cholera has again hit Koboko district and killed 2 people.
"From early Feb 2006 to date, we have registered 49 cases of cholera
infections. There was 1 death in the community and one at the health
facility," Dr Alfred Driwale, the district director of health services said
in an interview on Fri, 17 Mar 2006.
Daily Monitor has learnt that the latest infections were mainly in Midia
Sub-county and the town council. Driwale said he had already alerted the
WHO, United Nations Children's Emergency Fund and Ministry of Health. He
said the Health Ministry had given them intravenous fluids, drugs and other
medical supplies.
[Byline: Tabu Butagira]
--
